### 9. Timer Driver Processing (the "turn")

**File: `/home/bench/repos/tokio/tokio/src/runtime/time/mod.rs` (lines 296-337)**

**Handle::process_at_time() - The main timer processing loop:**

```rust
pub(self) fn process_at_time(&self, mut now: u64) {
    let mut waker_list = WakeList::new();
    let mut lock = self.inner.lock();

    // Poll the wheel for expired timers
    while let Some(entry) = lock.wheel.poll(now) {
        if let Some(waker) = unsafe { entry.fire(Ok(())) } {
            waker_list.push(waker);
            // ... batch wake to avoid deadlock ...
        }
    }

    // Update next wake time
    lock.next_wake = lock.wheel.poll_at()
        .map(|t| NonZeroU64::new(t).unwrap_or_else(|| NonZeroU64::new(1).unwrap()));

    drop(lock);
    waker_list.wake_all();  // Wake all timers outside the lock
}
```

The driver is invoked by `park_internal()` (lines 213-256) after the thread wakes from blocking.

### 10. Wheel Polling and Entry Expiration

**File: `/home/bench/repos/tokio/tokio/src/runtime/time/wheel/mod.rs` (lines 141-165)**

**Wheel::poll(now) - Main timer expiration:**
```rust
pub(crate) fn poll(&mut self, now: u64) -> Option<TimerHandle> {
    loop {
        // First, return any pending timers
        if let Some(handle) = self.pending.pop_back() {
            return Some(handle);
        }

        match self.next_expiration() {
            Some(ref expiration) if expiration.deadline <= now => {
                self.process_expiration(expiration);  // Move to lower level or pending
                self.set_elapsed(expiration.deadline);
            }
            _ => {
                self.set_elapsed(now);
                break;
            }
        }
    }
    self.pending.pop_back()
}
```

**Wheel::process_expiration() (lines 217-250):**
For each entry at the expiring slot:
1. Tries to mark it pending via `mark_pending(expiration.deadline)`
2. If successful, adds to `self.pending` queue
3. If not (deadline was updated), re-inserts at appropriate level

**TimerHandle::mark_pending() (lines 585-601 in entry.rs):**
