pub(super) unsafe fn mark_pending(&self, not_after: u64) -> Result<(), u64> {
    match unsafe { self.inner.as_ref().state.mark_pending(not_after) } {
        Ok(()) => {
            unsafe { self.inner.as_ref().set_registered_when(STATE_DEREGISTERED) };
            Ok(())
        }
        Err(tick) => {
            // Update and re-insert at new level if deadline changed
            unsafe { self.inner.as_ref().set_registered_when(tick) };
            Err(tick)
        }
    }
}
```

### 11. Firing the Timer and Waking

**File: `/home/bench/repos/tokio/tokio/src/runtime/time/entry.rs` (lines 210-231)**

**StateCell::fire():**
```rust
unsafe fn fire(&self, result: TimerResult) -> Option<Waker> {
    let cur_state = self.state.load(Ordering::Relaxed);
    if cur_state == STATE_DEREGISTERED {
        return None;  // Already fired
    }

    // SAFETY: driver lock held, only driver accesses result
    unsafe { self.result.with_mut(|p| *p = result) };

    self.state.store(STATE_DEREGISTERED, Ordering::Release);  // Mark as fired

    self.waker.take_waker()  // Extract and return the waker
}
```

The waker is extracted from `AtomicWaker::take_waker()` and returned.

**Back in Handle::process_at_time():**
Wakers are collected and called outside the driver lock to avoid deadlock.

### 12. Timeout Implementation

**File: `/home/bench/repos/tokio/tokio/src/time/timeout.rs`**

**Timeout structure (lines 172-182):**
